{% doc %}
  Outputs preconnect and dns-prefetch resource hints for known external origins
  used by all Shopify themes: the Shopify CDN and the Shopify font CDN.

  Placing these early in <head> allows the browser to establish TCP/TLS
  connections before it encounters the actual resource requests, shaving
  measurable time off first-byte latency for images and fonts.

  No parameters — hints are static and apply to every page.

  @example
    {%- render 'seo-resource-hints' -%}
{% enddoc %}
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://cdn.shopify.com" crossorigin>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.shopifycdn.com" crossorigin>
<link rel="dns-prefetch" href="https://cdn.shopify.com">
<link rel="dns-prefetch" href="https://fonts.shopifycdn.com">
